    "created_at": "2012-01-26T19:44:46Z",
    "updated_at": "2012-01-26T19:44:46Z",
    "body": "Agreed. Same old rule of thumb: if something needs to be provided to get a \"rustc foo.rc\" invocation to work at all, it shouldn't be an option. Command line options to rustc are things you should have the \"option\" of providing or omitting (or things like -L paths that you could not possibly write in the code itself, because it's invocation-environment-specific)\n",
